info.name: SocialMediaWebcare-Tracebuzz
info.description:
The SocialMediaWebcare API allows you to organise and manage your inbound and outbound social media channels traffic. ### Key highlights - **Security:** HTTPS, Oauth, Rate limit - **Versioning:** supports version-less API, version tight. If no version is provided (in header) it defaults to latest version. ## Getting Started --- ## [KPN Developer](https://developer.kpn.com/)
[Getting Started](https://developer.kpn.com/getting-started) --- Contact Support: Name: API Support Email: api_developer@kpn.com

request.description:
Use filters to retrieve results. You need to add the `profilename` and the `media`. If you are in the Traceboard dashboard, you can find the string with filters in the URL. All filters can be used within the string.

Example URL: `/test-profile/source:twitter/word:aloha/`

**media**

- twitter 
- facebook
- instagram
- google+plus
- linkedin
- whatsapp 
- blogs
- forums
- news
- web
- print
- rtv
- irischat
